DispositionOfAssetsDetail.AssetsDistriOrExpnssPaidDesc: South Bay Community Counseling Center paid Nixxit removal and donation serviced to come to the offices and remove all of the following items. These items could not be donated and were not sold in the sale of office furniture advertised. They include: 3 sofas, 2 large office desks, 3 rolling office arm chairs, 2 oak filing cabinets, 2-6 foot bookcases, 1 hexagonal table, 1 small refrigerator, 1 large office arm chair, 1 large framed picture, 1-3foot plant stand, 300 paper cups.
DispositionOfAssetsDetail.MethodOfFMVDeterminationTxt: Due to their wear and tear and age, these items did not sell and could not be donated, so their value is probably zero. Therefore, South Bay paid Nixxit to remove these items and they not only remove furniture and supplies but try to donate all items to families in need.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: South Bay community Counseling Center is continuing into 2023 to finish and complete all financial transactions with clients and insurance companies who still owe money to the organization.

South Bay Community Counseling Center donated, hauled to the dump, placed in trash, recycled, and paid for the disposal of all physical assets terminating all client/program services on October 31, 2022. Since there were still sizable accounts receivables, the organization continues to process this revenue from all past services rendered.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Clifford M Brothers, PhD, President, is the only Key Employee who received more than $100.00 in salary 100% from services rendered to clients.
One office was rented to a colleague for most of the year and this income is reported here as their rental income to South Bay community Counseling Center.

This amount totals bonuses received by Key Employees during the year, 2022. These bonuses represent accumulated bank account amounts from services rendered by these employees to maintain a surplus of bank balances to pay for various IRS, EDD, Malpractice Insurance, etc. and other expenses that were periodic and necessary to pay. This money should belong to the employees who deposited that money into the account.

This is the breakdown for these expenses: Overpayments returned to clients ($1308.00)(deducted from income), California filing fees ($95.00), costs to eliminated physical assets of the corporation ($879.00), Malpractice Insurance ($1864.00), cost of supplies organization ($60.00) totaling $4206.00.

All physical assets belonging to South Bay Community Counseling Center were eliminated by October 31, 2022 and the accounting for these assets are detailed in Schedule N. The remaining assets are reported as bank account balances. The corporation continues to receive revenue from clients and insurance companies to date.
Accounting adjustment probably for rounding up and down amounts in cents.
